In a saucepan, combine the sugar, white vinegar and 1 cup water. Bring to boil and stir until dissolved. In a small bowl, whisk together the salt, gelatin and 1/2 cup water. Add to saucepan, stir and cool. Once mixture is cool, add lemon juice, onion, celery, pecans, pimentos and asparagus. Mix well and place into favorite mold. Refrigerate until ready to serve.